commit.message:
Merge pull request #8 from nvinson/patch-1

Update handling of Linux LIBEXEC and DATADIR paths

Update handling of Linux LIBEXEC and DATADIR paths

Update the handling of the Linux LIBEXEC and DATADIR paths so that savagewheels
files are stored in ${LIBEXEC}/savagewheels and ${DATADIR}/savagewheels instead of
${LIBEXEC} and ${DATADIR}.  This change reduces the risk of filename collision with
other installed packages by placing savagewheels files in its own subdirectory.  This
change also provides a clean method of adding additional files to the LIBEXEC and
DATADIR tree if that ever becomes necessary.
Fix vehicles not loading on Windows
Remove a bunch of obsolete files
Produce a ZIP file when building Windows package

Merge pull request #7 from petarov/feature/linux-dirs

Feature/linux dirs

Fix self-extract build

`run.sh` script now used only when a self-extrcat build is invoked
via CPack.
Add Linux freedesktop entry and icon

Several fixes for Arch Linux PKGBUILD packaging

Use 'INSTALL_DATADIR' and 'INSTALL_LIBEXECDIR' in 'savagewheels.in',
so to be able to override them.

Package 'autos', 'graphics' and 'sound' dirs, only if available
in the bin/ dir. Self-extracting executables and PKGBUILD will use
that to construct the game package. Other pkg systems may just skip
it by not copying these folders in the game bin/ folder prior to
packaging.
Apply sys and user dirs patch by @nvinson
